reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Crafting made simple
reviews.reviewText: These STEM projects were a great find. I used them for my eighth graders and they loved them. They (mostly) read the directions and assembled alone, after getting a few instructions and some background knowledge. The price was fair for the item, and the material was well put together. The excitement of putting a craft together using critical thinking skills, troubleshooting, self- correcting, and seeing the vehicle in motion, was a wonderful experience.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My 11 year old son is really into robotics. So I bought his this kit and he had a great time putting them all together! It’s a fun learning project!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My son loves these sets and they are a great value for the price. This set has some instructions that are a little hard to follow for kids. They are not detailed and say basic things like "put together like in the picture". We have had 1 piece break because it did not fit well and when my son tried to push it in it snapped. I had to glue back together. That said, he loves them anyway!

reviews.reviewText: My 7 year old grandson really enjoyed putting together. This is great for beginners who love to build. The simplicity of the actual working gears made it easy as well as exciting to see it work! We have three more to put together. Great value.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars hard to assemble
reviews.reviewText: I gifted this to my 6 year old nephew and it was pretty impossible for him to assemble on his own. I think the age rating is for 8 years and up. It was still pretty difficult as an adult to assemble them as well. The included screws are very tiny and easy to loose. He enjoyed the cars once built but likely will not purchase again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Got this for my 8 year old son for Christmas and he was able to do it on his own! Which is something I really like because I can’t be there every 10 seconds helping. It was a great gift!
